/*
==================================================
SECTION 2: TASK STATES
==================================================
*/

##Task States - All 9 Types##

[ ] Unchecked task - pending work
[•] In progress task - actively working on this
[√] Completed task - finished with checkmark
[x] Completed task - finished with x mark
[!] Urgent task - needs immediate attention
[-] Skipped task - decided not to do this
[.] On hold task - paused for now
[+] Added task - newly added to the list
[?] Question task - needs clarification

##End##

/*
==================================================
SECTION 3: PRIORITY LEVELS
==================================================
*/

##Priority Levels##

[!0] CRITICAL - Drop everything and fix this now
[!1] HIGH - Do this very soon
[!2] MEDIUM - Normal priority task
[!3] LOW - When you have time

##End##

/*
==================================================
SECTION 4: INDENT LEVELS
==================================================
*/

##Indent Levels - 4 Levels Deep##

[ ] Level 0 task (no indent)
    [ ] Level 1 task (4 spaces)
        [ ] Level 2 task (8 spaces)
            [ ] Level 3 task (12 spaces)

[•] Level 0 in progress
    [•] Level 1 in progress
        [•] Level 2 in progress
            [•] Level 3 in progress

[√] Level 0 completed
    [√] Level 1 completed
        [√] Level 2 completed
            [√] Level 3 completed

[!] Level 0 urgent
    [!] Level 1 urgent
        [!] Level 2 urgent
            [!] Level 3 urgent

##End##

/*
==================================================
SECTION 5: LIST STYLES
==================================================
*/

##Dash Lists##

- Dash list item one
- Dash list item two
    - Nested dash level 1
    - Another nested dash
        - Deep nested dash level 2
            - Even deeper dash level 3

##End##

##Arrow Lists##

-> Arrow indicates flow or sequence
-> Next step in the process
    -> Sub-step here
    -> Another sub-step
        -> Detailed step
            -> Very detailed

##End##

##Thick Arrow Lists##

=> Thick arrow for emphasis
=> Important point to make
    => Supporting point
        => Detail here

##End##

##Asterisk Lists##

* Asterisk item one
* Asterisk item two
    * Nested asterisk
        * Deep asterisk

##End##

##Bullet Lists##

• Bullet point one
• Bullet point two
    • Nested bullet
        • Deep bullet

##End##

##Numbered Lists##

1. First numbered item
2. Second numbered item
3. Third numbered item
    1. Nested first
    2. Nested second
        1. Deep nested one
        2. Deep nested two

##End##

##Sub-Numbered Lists##

1.1. Sub-numbered item
1.2. Another sub-item
1.3. Third sub-item
    2.1. Indented sub-numbered
    2.2. Another indented
        3.1.1. Triple sub-numbered

##End##

